content:
To delete a dashboard, it's a good idea to do so when you no longer need it. 

Available in: Essentials, Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

To delete dashboards: 
- Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards (If the dashboard is in a private folder.)
- Edit My Dashboards (If the dashboard is in a shared folder.)

To delete dashboards created by another user: Manage Dashboards in Public Folders

Deleting a dashboard deletes the widgets within it, but custom reports aren't deleted. Deleted dashboards are moved to the Recycle Bin.

In Lightning Experience:
- On the Analytics tab or the Dashboards tab, find the dashboard and select Delete.
- Open the dashboard and select Delete.

In Salesforce Classic:
- Click the Dashboards tab.
- Click Go To Dashboards List.
- Choose the folder where the dashboard is stored.
- Click Del next to the name of the dashboard.
title: Deleting Dashboards in Salesforce
